WEBVTT

1
00:00:20.230 --> 00:00:22.230
In 1998. a growable neurochip
was made at Harima Science City.

2
00:00:22.230 --> 00:00:23.610
Its cells are dying
due to excessive growth.

3
00:00:23.610 --> 00:00:25.360
The fibers have grown to terminals
composed of galactose-infused polystyrene

4
00:00:25.360 --> 00:00:26.870
derivatives. distorting the thin
membrane the terminals are printed on.

5
00:00:27.400 --> 00:00:29.740
That same month. cyberbrain technology
begins shifting to a micromachine base.

6
00:00:29.740 --> 00:00:31.660
In 2028. neurochips are widely
used in robots and AI.

7
00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:41.040
In the near future. electrons and light race back and forth

8
00:00:32.950 --> 00:00:41.040
through corporate nets that blanket the globe.

9
00:00:33.860 --> 00:00:41.040
but the notions of nationality and ethnicity still cling to life
despite the spread of technology.

10
00:00:36.570 --> 00:00:41.040
A strange corporate collective state lying
 in a corner of Asia…

11
00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:43.040
Japan Nihon. Nippon
Island nation located in East Asia.

12
00:00:43.040 --> 00:00:44.010
Total area. 377.815 square km.
Total population. 76 million (as of 2029).

13
00:00:44.040 --> 00:00:46.340
MARCH 5. 2029

14
00:00:44.540 --> 00:00:46.380
NIIHAMA PREFECTURE ARTIFICIAL ISLAND
METROPOLIS OF NEWPORT CITY

15
00:00:52.050 --> 00:00:55.100
<i>Why the sudden interest
in silicon deposits?</i><i></i>

16
00:00:57.060 --> 00:01:00.980
<i>It's important enough that it will
guarantee that my government</i><i></i>

17
00:01:00.980 --> 00:01:05.020
<i>will stay out of your country's official
policy of not recognizing secessionists.</i><i></i>

18
00:01:05.020 --> 00:01:09.900
<i>Our stated position is that we provide aid
once independence is recognized.</i><i></i>

19
00:01:09.900 --> 00:01:12.570
<i>so this will not conflict
with our own trade interests.</i><i></i>

20
00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:15.660
<i>We will work through
a third-party country.</i><i></i>

21
00:01:18.450 --> 00:01:21.410
Excellent. After all. if a slave state
is negligent in its service.

22
00:01:21.420 --> 00:01:24.210
the master country will starve.

23
00:01:24.210 --> 00:01:27.510
Our manpower shortage will really give
the slave trade a huge boost.

24
00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:31.130
I must admit this does deviate
 somewhat from our socialist ideals.

25
00:01:31.130 --> 00:01:34.800
Despite all your country's
protestations of being capitalists.

26
00:01:34.800 --> 00:01:37.810
the truth is that you're
the ideal socialist state!

27
00:01:40.310 --> 00:01:41.600
What's keeping Team 2?!

28
00:01:43.600 --> 00:01:45.190
Is it the union again?

29
00:01:45.190 --> 00:01:47.610
They say there's been
 a bomb threat!

30
00:01:47.610 --> 00:01:49.490
We've finished evacuating
the civilians. sir.

31
00:01:53.990 --> 00:01:56.950
<i>Major. Public Security is
 ready to go.</i><i></i>

32
00:01:57.280 --> 00:01:59.950
I know.
 for crying out loud…

33
00:01:59.950 --> 00:02:02.160
When you let an AI
handle the encryption.

34
00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:04.460
everyone and their mother
will be able to listen in.

35
00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:08.960
All right! Turn off
the building's electromagnetic shield!

36
00:02:14.640 --> 00:02:16.470
All teams. comms are open!

37
00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:17.760
Go for breach!

38
00:02:28.110 --> 00:02:29.320
What's going on?

39
00:02:31.690 --> 00:02:34.030
You let the likes of Public Security
surround us?

40
00:02:34.030 --> 00:02:35.110
You fools!

41
00:02:45.580 --> 00:02:46.960
Stay where you are!

42
00:02:47.630 --> 00:02:49.130
Who gave the order to 
open fire?!

43
00:02:51.010 --> 00:02:52.210
Hold it!

44
00:02:55.430 --> 00:02:56.800
And what do we have
 here?

45
00:02:56.800 --> 00:02:58.890
If it isn't the Far East
Trade Representative.

46
00:02:58.890 --> 00:03:01.430
the Vice-Minister of Commerce.
and an Executive of the union.

47
00:03:01.720 --> 00:03:03.680
Oh. it's just you. 
Aramaki.

48
00:03:03.680 --> 00:03:08.230
This will finally give me enough evidence
to send you packing to your home country.

49
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:11.070
I wouldn't count my chickens
so fast if I were you.

50
00:03:11.280 --> 00:03:14.240
Shall I have you sit in
on his deposition. Vice-Minister Ito?

51
00:03:14.490 --> 00:03:16.400
Just to make sure I have
a detailed account

52
00:03:16.410 --> 00:03:19.450
regarding the bombing that killed
the late Prime Minister

53
00:03:19.450 --> 00:03:21.410
and who leaked 
the conference location.

54
00:03:21.700 --> 00:03:23.120
It's all over…

55
00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:25.580
I'm afraid that won't
be possible. Aramaki.

56
00:03:25.580 --> 00:03:28.130
The Vice-Minister
will be joining me on my flight.

57
00:03:28.630 --> 00:03:31.000
His request for asylum
has been granted.

58
00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:32.750
and I have a 
signed affidavit. too.

59
00:03:32.760 --> 00:03:33.670
When?!

60
00:03:33.670 --> 00:03:35.590
I'm under no obligation
 to answer that.

61
00:03:35.880 --> 00:03:39.050
Under international law.
I have the authority to take him

62
00:03:39.050 --> 00:03:41.100
into protective custody 
and take him home.

63
00:03:41.100 --> 00:03:43.470
Then in accordance with
international anti-terrorism laws.

64
00:03:43.470 --> 00:03:44.890
we request his extradition!

65
00:03:45.390 --> 00:03:47.940
When the paperwork arrives.
we'll consider it.

66
00:03:48.350 --> 00:03:50.900
Mark my words. Vice-Minister.
you'll be killed for this.

67
00:03:52.570 --> 00:03:56.150
My country is a civilized.
pacifist nation.

68
00:03:57.280 --> 00:03:58.570
Oh. is it now?

69
00:03:58.570 --> 00:03:59.450
Wha…

70
00:04:01.400 --> 00:04:03.910
UTILIZING LOW-VELOCITY
 SOFT-POINT EXPLOSIVE BULLETS

71
00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:12.960
Outside the window!

72
00:04:13.250 --> 00:04:15.050
There's nothing on
 the sensors!

73
00:04:28.640 --> 00:04:31.060
Is that 2902 thermal 
optical camo?!

74
00:04:31.730 --> 00:04:33.270
- Go get a tracker!
- Yes. sir!

75
00:04:40.700 --> 00:04:42.030
Here's the tracker. sir.

76
00:04:42.830 --> 00:04:44.370
It's too late.

77
00:04:48.830 --> 00:04:56.260
The next day. that woman appeared at the Minister of Internal Affairs' office.

78
00:04:52.710 --> 00:04:56.260
a kill order signed by the former Prime Minister in her hand...

79
00:04:57.720 --> 00:04:59.590
This woman. who gave her name
as "Motoko Kusanagi."

80
00:04:59.590 --> 00:05:01.800
proposed the formal creation
of a new special forces unit.

81
00:05:01.800 --> 00:05:03.350
citing the need for 
crisis management.

82
00:05:04.050 --> 00:05:06.890
That same day. the Minister of Internal
Affairs summoned Daisuke Aramaki.

83
00:05:06.890 --> 00:05:11.100
requesting that he devise a plan
to bring her into Public Security.

84
00:05:11.100 --> 00:05:13.190
Aramaki agrees.

85
00:05:13.190 --> 00:05:20.150
<i>People like her. you need to keep
on a tight leash.</i><i></i>

86
00:05:20.650 --> 00:05:25.320
<i>She requested the formation
of a special forces unit.</i><i></i>

87
00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:27.240
<i>Just like you did.</i><i></i>

88
00:07:02.710 --> 00:07:03.840
APRIL 10. 2029

89
00:07:08.260 --> 00:07:15.310
11:23 MESSAGE RECEIVED FROM ARAMAKI

90
00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:12.890
<i>Major. We got a job. Meet up with "Suisen"
in South Niihama Ward 4.</i><i></i>

91
00:07:13.560 --> 00:07:15.350
Funny. I don't remember
signing a contract.

92
00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:17.940
No contract. no deal!

93
00:07:18.400 --> 00:07:21.520
<i>The budget you requested to set up
your pet special forces unit</i><i></i>

94
00:07:21.530 --> 00:07:23.280
<i>was just passed by 
the National Council.</i><i></i>

95
00:07:23.280 --> 00:07:25.440
Fuchikoma!
Check the public record!

96
00:07:25.450 --> 00:07:26.530
Yes sir!

97
00:07:28.780 --> 00:07:31.740
Don't moan like that. damn it!
It grosses me out.

98
00:07:31.740 --> 00:07:35.540
An audio implant I had installed
the other day has a loose connection.

99
00:07:35.790 --> 00:07:37.040
<i>So what's up?</i><i></i>

100
00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:40.080
<i>You're really going through
with this deal with Public Security?</i><i></i>

101
00:07:40.090 --> 00:07:42.590
<i>If I'm gonna set up
an official special forces unit.</i><i></i>

102
00:07:42.590 --> 00:07:44.670
<i>I can't do it without the 
Bureau's help.</i><i></i>

103
00:07:44.670 --> 00:07:48.180
<i>That outfit's chief is no dummy.
We'll get swallowed up by Public Security.</i><i></i>

104
00:07:48.180 --> 00:07:53.220
Report located confirming passage
of budget by the 327th National Council!

105
00:07:54.390 --> 00:07:55.230
Well…

106
00:07:56.190 --> 00:07:59.730
I guess that means
he wasn't lying about that. anyway.

107
00:08:00.520 --> 00:08:03.650
Okay! Our round-the-clock
cherry blossom observation is canceled!

108
00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:04.940
Let's go to work!

109
00:08:05.400 --> 00:08:07.530
I thought I was gonna die 
of boredom.

110
00:08:08.860 --> 00:08:11.320
<i>Okay. people.
 stand by to brain-dive.</i><i></i>

111
00:08:11.330 --> 00:08:13.240
<i>We'll get tapped
 if we do it on comms.</i><i></i>

112
00:08:13.240 --> 00:08:15.830
<i>Do you want a sit-rep
before we get there or not?</i><i></i>

113
00:08:15.830 --> 00:08:16.910
<i>I'll use an attack barrier</i><i></i>

114
00:08:16.910 --> 00:08:19.620
<i>created by a wizard cyberbrain tech
to keep the hackers away.</i><i></i>

115
00:08:19.630 --> 00:08:21.710
<i>It's a hardcore type
that kills the hacker.</i><i></i>

116
00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:25.250
<i>When you feel a tingle. that's my
 Ghost line. Don't dive past there.</i><i></i>

117
00:08:25.260 --> 00:08:26.510
Yeah. fine.

118
00:08:39.480 --> 00:08:42.190
That brain of yours is in serious
need of decluttering.

119
00:08:42.560 --> 00:08:45.360
<i>Wow. Major. your prosthetic hands
are killing you. huh?</i><i></i>

120
00:08:45.360 --> 00:08:48.530
<i>What's this bitter taste I'm getting?
Some kind of sedative?</i><i></i>

121
00:08:48.530 --> 00:08:50.280
You got the 
intel for the op. right?

122
00:08:50.280 --> 00:08:53.200
If you're not out of my head in two seconds. 
I'll fry your brain cells!

123
00:08:53.200 --> 00:08:56.700
<i>I can't believe those clowns
dove that close to my damn Ghost.</i><i></i>

124
00:08:57.330 --> 00:09:02.080
<i>This is why I hate letting a bunch of
insensitive jerks into my brain!</i><i></i>

125
00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:06.600
SOUTH NIIHAMA WARD 4

126
00:09:06.600 --> 00:09:08.460
"Suisen" Field Command Post
 Ground Crew: 2 
 Command Post Admin Robot: 1

127
00:09:08.470 --> 00:09:11.220
SOUTH NIIHAMA 
CULTURAL CENTER

128
00:09:16.180 --> 00:09:17.850
So. what's the situation?

129
00:09:19.310 --> 00:09:22.310
Public Security currently has
the Sacred Citizen Relief Center

130
00:09:22.310 --> 00:09:23.940
under round-the-clock 
surveillance.

131
00:09:23.940 --> 00:09:25.310
Relief center?

132
00:09:25.320 --> 00:09:27.570
It's a welfare facility
that takes in war orphans.

133
00:09:27.570 --> 00:09:30.490
and provides them with a home. education.
and work opportunities.

134
00:09:30.490 --> 00:09:33.820
If that's the case. it has nothing
to do with us. Buh-bye.

135
00:09:33.820 --> 00:09:36.490
They have a
 Ghost controller. Major!

136
00:09:36.660 --> 00:09:37.910
Whoa. old school.

137
00:09:37.910 --> 00:09:39.870
To boost the effectiveness
of the brainwashing.

138
00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:42.620
they also appear to be developing
a new type of Ghost key.

139
00:09:42.620 --> 00:09:45.330
You had a hacker poke around
and they came up empty. huh?

140
00:09:45.340 --> 00:09:47.090
So. what? Steal it?
 Kill them?

141
00:09:47.210 --> 00:09:48.500
Nothing of the sort!

142
00:09:48.510 --> 00:09:52.050
Your objective is to subdue them
if necessary and arrest them.

143
00:09:52.180 --> 00:09:54.220
Without any evidence or
 a warrant?

144
00:09:54.220 --> 00:09:55.800
We got a hit.
 that much is certain!

145
00:09:56.810 --> 00:10:00.600
<i>Is their plan to bait me into attacking
the place and then go after me in court?</i><i></i>

146
00:10:00.850 --> 00:10:02.020
<i>Hell if I know.</i><i></i>

147
00:10:02.850 --> 00:10:03.900
Sheesh!

148
00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:07.320
<i>Doing half-assed stuff like this
won't get us anywhere.</i><i></i>

149
00:10:07.320 --> 00:10:09.230
<i>Is Ape-face trying to
 sabotage me?</i><i></i>

150
00:10:10.990 --> 00:10:16.240
<i>The relief center
is a happy. happy place!</i><i></i>

151
00:10:16.240 --> 00:10:21.290
<i>The teachers are oh
 so nice!</i><i></i>

152
00:10:21.660 --> 00:10:24.080
<i>The meals are the best.</i><i></i>

153
00:10:24.370 --> 00:10:25.750
The beds are soft as 
clouds!

154
00:10:25.750 --> 00:10:27.170
And even the work 
is fun!

155
00:10:27.170 --> 00:10:32.630
<i>We're so lucky to get
rice gruel every day!</i><i></i>

156
00:10:34.470 --> 00:10:36.970
We humbly thank you.
 School-Master!

157
00:10:37.140 --> 00:10:40.140
Thank you so very
 much!

158
00:10:40.810 --> 00:10:41.640
Eat up!

159
00:10:54.280 --> 00:10:56.360
If you don't like it. 
don't eat it!

160
00:10:56.370 --> 00:10:57.950
All of you. get to work!

161
00:10:58.990 --> 00:11:00.660
Work for the food 
you ate!

162
00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:03.500
The bed you slept in!
And the work we give you!

163
00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:11.630
That looks painful.

164
00:11:12.130 --> 00:11:14.590
Why isn't the Human Rights Bureau
doing anything?

165
00:11:14.720 --> 00:11:17.720
If you don't want to work.
go to the learning course!

166
00:11:17.720 --> 00:11:21.010
And if you don't want to do either one.
I won't apply you for a Citizen's Card!

167
00:11:21.350 --> 00:11:23.020
They got him too. huh?

168
00:11:23.020 --> 00:11:25.100
I hope he can take 
what they dish out.

169
00:11:25.350 --> 00:11:27.310
Do you have a feed
from the learning course?

170
00:11:27.560 --> 00:11:28.980
Sorry. no.

171
00:11:28.980 --> 00:11:30.690
No?!

172
00:11:31.070 --> 00:11:34.820
<i>Major. I'm sending you a feed
from the learning course on line four.</i><i></i>

173
00:12:01.760 --> 00:12:03.850
The universe is falling 
on me!

174
00:12:03.850 --> 00:12:07.020
Hey! You're overflowing to the others!
Calm down!

175
00:12:07.020 --> 00:12:08.690
I can't take it anymore!

176
00:12:14.230 --> 00:12:17.030
It's just a plain
 old education device!

177
00:12:17.030 --> 00:12:19.860
Don't yank my chain!
"Ghost controller." my ass!

178
00:12:19.870 --> 00:12:21.910
Hang on. They've dispatched 
security to get him.

179
00:12:21.910 --> 00:12:23.280
Yeah. so what?

180
00:12:23.290 --> 00:12:24.990
Just before the feed
 cut out.

181
00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:28.420
didn't you feel like. "If they catch me.
at least it'll all be over"?

182
00:12:29.670 --> 00:12:33.000
<i>Togusa! Ishikawa! Plant the 
runaway kid with a baby spider.</i><i></i>

183
00:12:33.170 --> 00:12:34.210
<i>On it.</i><i></i>

184
00:12:35.510 --> 00:12:40.300
"If this goes sideways. you can retire
and the unit will go on." huh?

185
00:12:40.890 --> 00:12:44.430
I wouldn't get off that easy.
I appreciate the thought. though.

186
00:12:51.770 --> 00:12:55.150
<i>Look. Ishikawa…
I've got a bad feeling about this.</i><i></i>

187
00:12:55.150 --> 00:12:57.030
<i>Suck it up. Newbie.</i><i></i>

188
00:12:57.030 --> 00:13:00.700
<i>That female-ape has our balls
in her mighty grip.</i><i></i>

189
00:13:00.700 --> 00:13:01.990
<i>My hearing's mighty. too.</i><i></i>

190
00:13:02.280 --> 00:13:06.290
<i>How lucky we are to have such a young
and beautiful and kind squad leader!</i><i></i>

191
00:13:06.290 --> 00:13:07.120
<i>Good.</i><i></i>

192
00:13:22.840 --> 00:13:24.970
Circle around and
 head him off.

193
00:13:24.970 --> 00:13:25.890
Yes. sir.

194
00:13:31.600 --> 00:13:35.360
This guard will be in sleep mode
for 25 seconds. Newbie.

195
00:13:35.520 --> 00:13:38.570
Give the "Newbie" crap a rest!
I'm on it!

196
00:13:59.210 --> 00:14:00.470
<i>Major.</i><i></i>

197
00:14:00.670 --> 00:14:02.130
<i>The guards here</i><i></i>

198
00:14:02.130 --> 00:14:06.180
<i>are some seriously modified
Sagawa Heavy Industries type 2033s.</i><i></i>

199
00:14:06.180 --> 00:14:08.810
<i>Those are custom jobs used
by the military in artillery squads.</i><i></i>

200
00:14:08.810 --> 00:14:11.560
<i>They're just back-alley chop shop cyborgs
using that same model.</i><i></i>

201
00:14:11.560 --> 00:14:14.560
<i>They're also using government-issue
fiber optic nerves.</i><i></i>

202
00:14:14.810 --> 00:14:17.820
<i>That means that
they're on the government's payroll.</i><i></i>

203
00:14:17.980 --> 00:14:21.110
Are you sure you didn't get hit
with a simulated experience?

204
00:14:21.490 --> 00:14:24.610
My barrier is no cheap piece 
of junk.

205
00:14:25.120 --> 00:14:28.120
Either way. it'll be a scandal
if we storm the place.

206
00:14:28.120 --> 00:14:31.540
Who's gonna be the one to take the heat?
Some politician?

207
00:14:31.540 --> 00:14:34.790
Or us? Or those kids?

208
00:14:35.250 --> 00:14:37.540
He must've passed out
from low blood sugar or something.

209
00:14:37.540 --> 00:14:40.550
Too bad. three strikes
and it's brainwashing time.

210
00:14:41.970 --> 00:14:44.300
Sucks to be him.

211
00:14:47.050 --> 00:14:48.970
<i>Get ready to move in.
people!</i><i></i>

212
00:14:49.470 --> 00:14:52.980
A unit like us is a must
 in any era.

213
00:14:52.980 --> 00:14:54.810
So we have nothing 
to lose.

214
00:14:55.150 --> 00:14:56.850
Trying to create a 
scandal.

215
00:14:56.860 --> 00:14:59.020
Politicians trying
to screw each other over.

216
00:14:59.020 --> 00:15:00.690
Kids being brainwashed.

217
00:15:00.860 --> 00:15:04.860
Rooting out bastards who do this crap
is why I made a deal with Ape-face.

218
00:15:05.280 --> 00:15:07.200
So I say screw it. 
let's do this.

219
00:15:07.660 --> 00:15:09.950
A little voice 
is urging me on...

220
00:15:10.240 --> 00:15:12.120
That voice is my Ghost!

221
00:15:18.500 --> 00:15:20.670
<i>Seal off the 
drainage tunnel ASAP!</i><i></i>

222
00:15:21.760 --> 00:15:23.090
The kid has a bug
 on him.

223
00:15:23.630 --> 00:15:25.970
They're onto us!
Togusa. emergency evac!

224
00:15:27.340 --> 00:15:29.720
<i>Switching comms
over to attack barrier mode!</i><i></i>

225
00:15:30.350 --> 00:15:32.850
How did they even know
about the drainage tunnel?

226
00:15:32.850 --> 00:15:35.520
Do we have a leak?
Or was this really a trap?

227
00:15:39.650 --> 00:15:42.190
<i>Damage detected in 
pipe number 17.</i><i></i>

228
00:15:42.440 --> 00:15:43.860
<i>You two go check it out.</i><i></i>

229
00:15:51.370 --> 00:15:54.370
What are you doing?
You'll get fried by their attack barrier!

230
00:15:54.540 --> 00:15:55.460
I can't. I got locked--

231
00:16:01.040 --> 00:16:03.750
Let's go. Batou.
She was nothing but a speaker.

232
00:16:03.760 --> 00:16:05.380
Public Security will 
fix her up.

233
00:16:05.380 --> 00:16:08.340
And give her a whole new program
while they're at it?

234
00:16:08.340 --> 00:16:11.050
There's something sad
about these Ghostless puppets.

235
00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:15.100
Especially the type that 
bleeds red.

236
00:16:17.390 --> 00:16:18.850
That's strange.

237
00:16:18.850 --> 00:16:22.150
I didn't feel that last burst of defiance
you get when a Ghost is fried.

238
00:16:22.150 --> 00:16:24.860
Was it an artificial intelligence
that I roasted?

239
00:16:24.860 --> 00:16:26.110
We're up against pros!

240
00:16:26.820 --> 00:16:28.740
<i>Hey! What's the matter. 
Togusa?</i><i></i>

241
00:16:29.110 --> 00:16:30.240
<i>Togusa!</i><i></i>

242
00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:31.950
Togusa! Ow.

243
00:16:32.160 --> 00:16:33.280
Damn it!

244
00:16:33.280 --> 00:16:35.660
<i>This stupid audio implant
with the dumb loose connection!</i><i></i>

245
00:16:46.630 --> 00:16:48.430
Hey! Why are you just 
standing there?

246
00:16:49.090 --> 00:16:50.840
I… I can't go any further.

247
00:16:52.510 --> 00:16:55.430
This is a message
to not throw my life away.

248
00:16:56.020 --> 00:16:58.060
The war is over.

249
00:16:58.180 --> 00:16:59.640
I'm sick of killing people!

250
00:16:59.640 --> 00:17:02.770
Hmph! I'm not a gutless wimp 
like you!

251
00:17:02.770 --> 00:17:04.190
Fine. Die. then.

252
00:17:16.330 --> 00:17:18.200
Togusa is out cold!

253
00:17:18.200 --> 00:17:19.870
Smack him awake
and get away from there!

254
00:17:19.870 --> 00:17:22.000
- To leave?
- To storm the place. obviously!

255
00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:24.960
Our princess
is one hell of a slave driver.

256
00:17:38.730 --> 00:17:41.060
Hang on. 
that's Ishikawa's Fuchikoma!

257
00:17:41.060 --> 00:17:42.230
What's gotten into him?

258
00:17:44.900 --> 00:17:48.110
Why does his thing have such
a lousy targeting system?

259
00:17:48.360 --> 00:17:50.900
Ishikawa! Snap out of it. 
damn it!

260
00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:57.540
Major! Their security has a 
Ghost controller!

261
00:17:58.660 --> 00:18:01.620
Fuchikoma! Close the channel!
Go to lockout mode!

262
00:18:25.770 --> 00:18:28.440
<i>He was able to get in before 
my attack barrier could react!</i><i></i>

263
00:18:28.610 --> 00:18:29.650
Fuchikoma!

264
00:18:30.190 --> 00:18:33.360
Back-trace his signal path!
Nail his ass with an attack barrier!

265
00:18:33.570 --> 00:18:34.740
Yes sir!

266
00:18:40.040 --> 00:18:41.790
You son of a… 
You'll pay for that!

267
00:18:52.170 --> 00:18:55.390
Having a substitute barrier
 running saved my ass.

268
00:18:55.680 --> 00:18:58.510
I have to neutralize
that weird commander of theirs.

269
00:20:01.780 --> 00:20:04.200
No sight. no heat. 
no sound…

270
00:20:05.250 --> 00:20:07.330
A Kyo-Re Invisibility Cape?!

271
00:20:12.800 --> 00:20:14.510
Okay. enough! I surrender!

272
00:20:14.710 --> 00:20:16.550
Please. just don't damage 
my brain!

273
00:20:16.880 --> 00:20:19.140
You and me. 
we're both just doing a job!

274
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:22.220
The Ghost infiltration key
and Ghost controller.

275
00:20:22.220 --> 00:20:23.850
Fine. I'll hand them over!

276
00:20:24.390 --> 00:20:27.600
You're under arrest
for cyberbrain ethics violations.

277
00:20:27.600 --> 00:20:30.020
Are you kidding me?!
You're Public Security?

278
00:20:35.690 --> 00:20:39.740
Y-You came to take us away 
from here. right?

279
00:20:39.740 --> 00:20:42.490
Huh? What do you 
even want?

280
00:20:42.490 --> 00:20:45.160
Are you gonna mooch off of welfare
without meeting your obligations

281
00:20:45.160 --> 00:20:47.250
to society as you're being
brainwashed by trashy media?

282
00:20:47.500 --> 00:20:50.500
At the expense of all the countries
that haven't been as quick to rebuild.

283
00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:52.500
You have a Ghost. too. 
don't you. kid?

284
00:20:52.670 --> 00:20:55.920
You have a brain in that head of yours.
And you can access a cyberbrain.

285
00:20:59.430 --> 00:21:00.970
Make your own future!

286
00:21:07.390 --> 00:21:11.230
<i>Yes. that was one of the government's
brainwashing facilities.</i><i></i>

287
00:21:11.350 --> 00:21:14.690
<i>They were starting to go rogue.
so I had you make an example of them.</i><i></i>

288
00:21:14.890 --> 00:21:17.240
10 APRIL 2029                20:26

289
00:21:15.390 --> 00:21:17.240
SOMEWHERE

290
00:21:15.320 --> 00:21:17.030
<i>The Boss says he wants
 a word.</i><i></i>

291
00:21:17.860 --> 00:21:19.150
<i>I'll transfer you.</i><i></i>

292
00:21:20.280 --> 00:21:25.030
<i>Ah. Major Kusanagi. You went
a tad bit overboard. don't you think?</i><i></i>

293
00:21:25.030 --> 00:21:27.740
I think you knew that
we would make a mess.

294
00:21:27.750 --> 00:21:32.120
<i>That request I also got from you.
What was it again?</i><i></i>

295
00:21:32.130 --> 00:21:35.540
<i>Ah. yes. About the forming
 of that unit.</i><i></i>

296
00:21:35.550 --> 00:21:39.670
<i>When things like this happen…
How can I put this?</i><i></i>

297
00:21:39.880 --> 00:21:41.880
<i>It makes things difficult.</i><i></i>

298
00:21:42.010 --> 00:21:44.680
<i>Of course. if you were to be
a team player.</i><i></i>

299
00:21:45.180 --> 00:21:47.640
<i>perhaps I could find a way
to afford you some leeway.</i><i></i>

300
00:21:47.640 --> 00:21:49.140
Give me that
 Ghost infiltration key.

301
00:21:49.520 --> 00:21:52.850
Mr. Minister? Might I trouble you
for a direct connection for two seconds?

302
00:21:52.850 --> 00:21:54.060
<i>Sure.
 that would be fine.</i><i></i>

303
00:21:58.280 --> 00:22:00.650
If staying here means being
a Public Security errand girl.

304
00:22:00.650 --> 00:22:02.110
I'll find another line
 of work.

305
00:22:03.360 --> 00:22:04.820
Chief?

306
00:22:07.870 --> 00:22:09.870
I suppose 
it wasn't meant to be.

307
00:22:13.250 --> 00:22:15.830
Join me for a drink!
Batou. write up the report.

308
00:22:15.840 --> 00:22:16.960
Blech!

309
00:22:16.960 --> 00:22:18.880
Hm? Where'd Togusa go?

310
00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:21.550
After you chewed him out.
he left. bawling his eyes out.

311
00:22:21.550 --> 00:22:23.890
That guy is such a 
newbie!
